Cook the spaghetti, drain well, put in a large bowl and toss with a little oil. Set aside. Asian Citrus Peanut Sauce Combine the JIF(R) peanut butter, orange juice, lemon juice, soy sauce and sugar in a medium bowl. Whisk until very well blended. In a large, deep-sided skillet, heat 1/2 cup CRISCO(R) Canola Oil over medium heat. Add the chopped pepper, chopped onion, and minced garlic, cook about 1 minute. Add the broccoli florets and stir, add the Asian Citrus Peanut Sauce, and stir. Continue to cook stirring often, until the broccoli is cooked to your liking. Toss with the pasta. Serve at room temperature. Refrigerate if not served immediately. Will keep refrigerated about 2 days.